long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1151235 mscz file
Description of problem: After upgrading from mscore-2.0.2-1.fc24 to mscore-2.0.3-1.fc24.x86_64 and opening some .mscz file, there is a weird note presentation of the score. (Very narrow). I didn't see that in mscore-2.0.2-1.fc24, where the score is displayed correctl. The mscz file will be attached. Additionally, I see a weird error message on the terminal:
/usr/bin/mscore <.mscz file> QDir::mkpath: Empty or null file name QDir::mkpath: Empty or null file name QDir::mkpath: Empty or null file name QDir::mkpath: Empty or null file name QIODevice::read (QFile, ":/fonts/mscore/glyphnames.json"): device not open QIODevice::read (QFile, ":/fonts/mscore/metadata.json"): device not open QIODevice::read (QFile, ":/fonts/bravura/glyphnames.json"): device not open QIODevice::read (QFile, ":/fonts/bravura/metadata.json"): device not open
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 2.0.3-1
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1.see description 2. 3.
Actual results: weird score representation
Expected results:
Additional info:

I forget to report: The attached file has been made with the upstream version 3.0.0 (unstable), and if trying to open it with mscore-2.0.3-1 I get the error msg: "File can't be read. This score was stored with a newer version of mscore! Ignore or cancel". If I answer with"ignore", I 'm experiencing the described effect.
Doing exactly the same with mscore-2.0.2-1 as described above, this .mscz file will be opened correctly!
mscore-2.0.3-2.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-94d90fbf54

Created attachment 1154773 Same problem with an mscz file not made with the mscore upstream version
This score file hadn't been edited by the upstream mscore version, but shows the same symptoms (very narrow notes), so it does notonly be a problem with imported mscore-3.0.0 files.
